## 🎛️ Pin Mapping (Arduino Pro Micro / Nano / Uno)

> ⚠️ **CRITICAL WARNING:** Always unplug the FlySky receiver's signal wire from the Arduino's hardware **RX pin** before uploading the code, or the compilation/upload process will fail!

| Arduino Pin | Connection Component | Controller Map / Input Action |
| :---: | :--- | :--- |
| **RX (Serial)** | FlySky Receiver (i-BUS Out) | Master Wireless Control (Ch1, Ch2, Ch3) |
| **D2 (Soft RX)** | HC-05 Bluetooth -> **TXD** | App Smartphone Telemetry (Read) |
| **D3 (Soft TX)** | HC-05 Bluetooth -> **RXD** | App Smartphone Telemetry (Write) |
| **D5** | Left Motor -> **RPWM_L** | Left Wheel Forward Drive |
| **D6** | Left Motor -> **LPWM_L** | Left Wheel Backward Drive |
| **D9** | Right Motor -> **RPWM_R** | Right Wheel Forward Drive |
| **D10** | Right Motor -> **LPWM_R** | Right Wheel Backward Drive |

*Note: Make sure to bridge the `R_EN` and `L_EN` pins of both BTS7960 drivers directly to the **5V (VCC)** power line to keep them active.*

